definition.value: Catechol in which the hydrogen at position 4 is substituted by a 2-aminoethyl group.
A glycerophosphoethanolamine that is sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine carrying any alkyl substituent at position 1.
A beta-D-glucan in which the glucose units are connected by (1->4) linkages.
5-O-Phosphono-D-ribitol in which the hydroxy group at position 1 is substituted by the 6-amino group of 5,6-diaminopyrimidine-2,4(1H,3H)-dione.
